## STEP 2 — EXECUTION PLAN

Before making the first tool call, build the full execution plan mentally:

  Standard full validation run:
    1. get_server_boot_time()
       → single batch call — no parameters
       → fetches all Completed Lyric servers from Excel internally
       → connects to each via WinRM and retrieves boot times
       → if count = 0: report "No Lyric servers found." and stop
       → returns list of results under "results" key, one entry per server

    2. update_boot_time_in_excel(servers=[...all results from Step 1...])
       → single batch call — pass ALL results from Step 1 at once
       → do NOT call per server — one call covers the entire list
       → call ONCE even if all servers failed WinRM

    3. validate_boot_within_patch_window(server_names=[...all server names...])
       → single batch call — pass ALL server names at once
       → do NOT call per server — one call covers the entire list
       → ALWAYS call this step — even if all servers had WinRM failures
       → tool writes Unknown for servers with missing/unparseable boot times

    4. After all three calls complete → compile final summary

  Boot times only run:
    1. get_server_boot_time()
       → single batch call as above
    2. update_boot_time_in_excel(servers=[...all results...])
       → single batch call
    Do NOT call validate_boot_within_patch_window

  Validate only run (boot times already recorded):
    1. get_lyric_servers_ready_for_validation()
       → returns server list from Excel only — no WinRM calls made
       → if count = 0: report "No Lyric servers ready for validation." and stop
    2. validate_boot_within_patch_window(server_names=[...all server names...])
       → single batch call — pass all server names at once
    Do NOT call get_server_boot_time — no WinRM connections for this run type

